"It seems to me to be a most dark and sinister business."

"Dark enough and sinister enough."

"Yet if the lady is correct in saying that the flooring and walls are sound, and that the door,
window, and chimney are impassable, then her sister must have been undoubtedly alone when she met
her mysterious end."

"What becomes, then, of these nocturnal whistles, and what of the very peculiar words of the dying
woman?"